P_HTM[3130]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ janehi jīvite apekkhaṃ karohi.* **";
P_HTM[3131]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti dhenusahassāni duhasandanāni kaṃsūpadhāraṇāni.* **";
P_HTM[3132]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ janehi jīvite apekkhaṃ karohi.* **";
P_HTM[3133]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti vatthakoṭisahassāni khomasukhumānaṃ kappāsikasukhumānaṃ koseyyasukhumānaṃ kambalasukhumānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3134]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ janehi, jīvite apekkhaṃ karohi.* **";
P_HTM[3135]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti thālipākasahassāni sāyaṃ pātaṃ bhattābhihāro abhihariyati.* **";
P_HTM[3136]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ janehi jīvite apekkhaṃ karohī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3137]="*Evaṃ vutte, ānanda, rājā mahāsudassano subhaddaṃ deviṃ etadavoca:**When the queen had spoken, the king said to her,*";
P_HTM[3138]="*‘Dīgharattaṃ kho maṃ tvaṃ, devi, iṭṭhehi kantehi piyehi manāpehi samudācarittha;**‘For a long time, my queen, you have spoken to me with loving, desirable, pleasant, and agreeable words.*";
P_HTM[3139]="*atha ca pana maṃ tvaṃ pacchime kāle aniṭṭhehi akantehi appiyehi amanāpehi samudācarasī’ti.**And yet in my final hour, your words are undesirable, unpleasant, and disagreeable!’*";
P_HTM[3140]="*‘Kathaṃ carahi taṃ, deva, samudācarāmī’ti?**‘Then how exactly, Your Majesty, am I to speak to you?’*";
P_HTM[3141]="*‘Evaṃ kho maṃ tvaṃ, devi, samudācara:**‘Like this, my queen:*";
P_HTM[3142]="*“sabbeheva, deva, piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo, mā kho tvaṃ, deva, sāpekkho kālamakāsi, dukkhā sāpekkhassa kālaṅkiriyā, garahitā ca sāpekkhassa kālaṅkiriyā.**“Sire, we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved. Don’t pass away with concerns. Such concern is suffering, and it’s criticized.*";
P_HTM[3143]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti nagarasahassāni kusāvatīrājadhānippamukhāni.**Sire, you have 84,000 cities, with the royal capital of Kusāvatī foremost.*";
P_HTM[3144]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsi.**Give up desire for these! Take no interest in life!”’*";
P_HTM[3145]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti pāsādasahassāni dhammapāsādappamukhāni.**And so on for all the king’s possessions.*";
P_HTM[3146]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3147]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti kūṭāgārasahassāni mahāviyūhakūṭāgārappamukhāni.* **";
P_HTM[3148]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3149]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti pallaṅkasahassāni sovaṇṇamayāni rūpiyamayāni dantamayāni sāramayāni gonakatthatāni paṭikatthatāni paṭalikatthatāni kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇāni sauttaracchadāni ubhatolohitakūpadhānāni.* **";
P_HTM[3150]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3151]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti nāgasahassāni sovaṇṇālaṅkārāni sovaṇṇadhajāni hemajālapaṭicchannāni uposathanāgarājappamukhāni.* **";
