P_HTM[3170]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsī”’ti.* **";
P_HTM[3171]="*Evaṃ vutte, ānanda, subhaddā devī parodi assūni pavattesi.**When the king had spoken, Queen Subhaddā cried and burst out in tears.*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Atha kho, ānanda, subhaddā devī assūni puñchitvā rājānaṃ mahāsudassanaṃ etadavoca:**Wiping away her tears, the queen said to the king:*";
P_HTM[3173]="*‘Sabbeheva, deva, piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo aññathābhāvo, mā kho tvaṃ, deva, sāpekkho kālamakāsi, dukkhā sāpekkhassa kālaṅkiriyā, garahitā ca sāpekkhassa kālaṅkiriyā.**‘Sire, we must be parted and separated from all we hold dear and beloved. Don’t pass away with concerns. Such concern is suffering, and it’s criticized.*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti nagarasahassāni kusāvatīrājadhānippamukhāni.**Sire, you have 84,000 cities, with the royal capital of Kusāvatī foremost.*";
P_HTM[3175]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsi.**Give up desire for these! Take no interest in life!’*";
P_HTM[3176]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti pāsādasahassāni dhammapāsādappamukhāni.**And she continued, listing all the king’s possessions.*";
P_HTM[3177]="*Ettha, deva, chandaṃ pajaha jīvite apekkhaṃ mākāsi.* **";
P_HTM[3178]="*Imāni te, deva, caturāsīti kūṭāgārasahassāni mahāviyūhakūṭāgārappamukhāni.* **";
